                            <comment id="21468" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 27 Dec 2006 09:17:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that we do &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; guarantee full compatibility of protected template methods between Spring 1.2 and 2.0 in the first place. That said, I agree that a deprecated method at least in UrlFilenameViewController would be appropriate (to immediately raise a warning when recompiling custom subclasses.) I guess it&apos;s not as important in AbstractUrlViewController, since what changed there is an abstract template method: Direct subclasses will immediately notice anyway, since they can&apos;t recompile without implementing the new template method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="21469" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 27 Dec 2006 09:29:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve extracted a &quot;getViewNameForUrlPath(String)&quot; method in UrlFilenameViewController, for full compatibility of the UrlFilenameViewController class with Spring 1.2.8. (Note that the more typical customization hook, the &quot;extractViewNameFromUrlPath&quot; method, was compatible already.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="21471" author="zznate" created="Wed, 27 Dec 2006 09:58:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Juergen, thank you for such a fast turn around! So fast, in fact, I just submitted bug &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2988&quot; title=&quot;UrlFilenameViewController incorrectly parses the view name from the path - makes incorrect statement to such in javadoc as well&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2988&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-2988&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with a patch file. Hopefully it is of use to you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
